You are working on ROAM, an AI-powered travel planning app built with React Native + Expo Router.

CRITICAL RULES:
- NO EMOJIS in UI code. Use colored dots, text pills, or lucide-react-native icons.
- NEVER call Anthropic API directly from client code. All AI goes through supabase/functions/claude-proxy/.
- NEVER put secrets in EXPO_PUBLIC_ vars (except Supabase anon key and public API keys).
- ALWAYS use immutable patterns. Never mutate state.
- Files under 800 lines. Functions under 50 lines. Nesting under 4 levels.

DESIGN SYSTEM (import from lib/constants.ts):
- COLORS: bg=#080F0A, sage=#7CAF8A, cream=#F5EDD8, coral=#E8614A, accentGold=#C9A84C
- FONTS: Cormorant Garamond Bold (headers), DM Sans (body), DM Mono (mono/labels)
- Dark-only UI. All cards use bgCard with border color.

ARCHITECTURE:
- app/ = Expo Router screens (file-based routing)
- lib/ = Business logic, API clients, utilities
- components/features/ = Feature-specific UI components
- components/ui/ = Reusable design system components
- supabase/functions/ = Deno edge functions (server-side)
- supabase/migrations/ = SQL migrations with RLS

KEY PATTERNS:
- State: Zustand store in lib/store.ts
- Auth: Supabase auth + guest mode (lib/guest.ts)
- Subscriptions: RevenueCat (lib/revenue-cat.ts)
- Pro gating: lib/pro-gate.ts
- Web compatibility: lib/haptics.ts and lib/view-shot.ts are web-safe shims

BEFORE COMMITTING:
- Run: npx tsc --noEmit
- Check: No hardcoded secrets
- Verify: RLS policies use auth.uid() not true
